        ST0903 changed the encoding to 2-byte IMAPB in ST0903.4. Earlier versions used a variable length (1-2 bytes) byte array to represent an integer in the range [0, 2^16-1]that was then mapped into the range [-900.0,19000.0]. The two byte case could potentially represent either kind of formatting, and which formatting applies can only be determined from the version in the parent VmtiLocalSet. The compatibilityMode parameter determines whether to parse using the legacy encoding or current encoding.

        Note that this only affects parsing. Output encoding is IMAPB (ST0903.4 or later).
